UPDATE designers SET biography = 'Belgian designer of refined interiors and sculptural furniture, handcrafted in Belgium. Trained at Saint-Lucas School of Arts in Ghent and Domus Academy in Milan, she began her professional life at RR Interieur, one of Belgium''s most respected design destinations, which gave her early work its first platform and audience.

https://res.cloudinary.com/dif1oamtj/image/upload/v1776053286/Bieke_casteleyn_1_1_kr6jea.jpg | Bieke Casteleyn | left

Bieke Casteleyn founded her eponymous brand in 2015, driven by a single, quietly radical conviction: the everyday courage to look at things from a different perspective. Her vision bring high-end serenity through innovative materials and harmonious forms.

https://res.cloudinary.com/dif1oamtj/image/upload/v1776053284/Bieke_designing_3_u2uzbd.jpg | It starts with a drawing | right

Her debut collection, Out of Line, asked a disarmingly simple question: why does a table need to be round, oval, or square? The answer was a series of organically shaped furniture pieces — curved, irregular, entirely her own — that looked less like manufactured objects and more like something shaped by natural forces. That collection remains the core of her work today, now expanded across furniture, objects and lighting.

Bieke''s aesthetic lives in the tension between restraint and boldness: organic forms held in careful balance, timeless neutrals punctuated by expressive colour, sculptural presence grounded in everyday function.

Every piece is handmade in her own Belgian atelier, built up in layers of cement-based stuc or lacquer finish, then meticulously examined before receiving her personal seal of approval. The process is slow by design. Each object is conceived to be passed from one generation to the next — not a purchase, but an inheritance.' WHERE slug = 'bieke-casteleyn';